I absolutely love the following poem. I received it when I was 18
years old and struggling with relationships and all kinds of other
junk. I don't even remember who gave it to me. This poem and others
like it have kept me &quot;centered&quot;. Being &quot;centered&quot; is key to me:
staying in the here and now and knowing that Jesus and those He has
given me to love me are with me each step at a time now and throughout
eternity. Enjoy.

&quot;I'M HIDING&quot;
(Anonymous)

&quot;I'm hiding, Lord
And tired of the masquerade.
The costume bag has been exhausted.
The masks are worn and ragged.
365 days of Halloween is not a treat.

I'm hiding because I'm frightened . . .
Of the smiles covering tears
And paint covering years,
And just the whole game of hide and seek.

This morning I put the costume bag in the attic.
This afternoon I must venture out with no cover-ups,
No tricks and no gimmicks.
Just the timid, sensitive, caring individual You made me,
Seeking perhaps just one more
Who wants out of the game.
And together we go through life unafraid,
Seeing not only the surface, but beneath.
Sharing even the daydreams,
And the crazy, childlike fantasies Of life together.

Lord, smooth out the rough edges of the real me.

I've never played that role before.

Amen.&quot;

</POST>



